N-no problem.

285
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:39,400
Go.

286
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:40,640
Let's go.

287
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:45,040
Will they go to the dean?

288
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,120
Really?

289
00:18:57,520 --> 00:18:58,280
Class,

290
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:01,050
before we finish, I have an announcement.

291
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,240
The triennial

292
00:19:02,240 --> 00:19:03,920
citywide middle school drama competition

293
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:04,920
is starting soon.

294
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:07,080
The rules require

295
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:09,760
that the play cannot be negative

296
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,280
or vulgar.

297
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:13,680
The school will select one performance

298
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:14,720
from the junior high and tenth grade

299
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,400
to participate in the city competition.

300
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,080
Of course,

301
00:19:17,560 --> 00:19:19,360
if you think it'll interfere with your studies,

302
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:21,000
it's fine if you don't want to participate.

303
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:21,800
No, no, no.

304
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:22,920
Mr. Tian, we will participate.

305
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,200
We're in. We're in.

306
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,720
I knew you guys would want to join in.

307
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,200
All right. Since you are in tenth grade

308
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:30,960
and still have some free time,

309
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,280
I'll give you this chance.

310
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:35,000
Do you have any good suggestions for the theme?

311
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,560
The judges this time are no longer limited to adults.

312
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:39,640
The evaluation of peers

313
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:41,080
also accounts for a large proportion.

314
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,520
So our topic selection this time

315
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:45,160
must also take into account the preferences of young people.

316
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:46,800
I have also thought about this problem.

317
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,560
Xing Yaqi, what do you think?

318
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,080
Mr. Tian.

319
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:52,680
I personally prefer foreign movies.

320
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:55,120
And my favorite is "Gone with the Wind".

321
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:57,640
I think the plot in it is very good,

322
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:59,240
and the lines are also great.

323
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:01,320
If we can take some classic clips

324
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,920
and perform them,

325
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,730
I think it should be quite good.

326
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,520
Don't just say quite good.

327
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,720
If we do it, we should do the best, right?

328
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,440
Yes.

329
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:10,520
Mr. Tian.

330
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:13,320
I think domestic classics are also good.

331
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,520
'Dream of the Red Chamber' is pretty good.

332
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:16,440
If we add some music to it,

333
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:19,240
we can perform Jia Baoyu and Lin Daiyu's

334
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:20,640
poignant love story.

335
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:21,520
Come on.

336
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,800
Which girl in our class

337
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,200
looks like Lin Daiyu?

338
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:25,960
They look like Cheng Yaojin.

339
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,160
Once they're on stage,

340
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:30,000
"Brother Bao, where are you going?"

341
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,530
Isn't that ridiculous?

342
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,880
Don't you like 'A Chinese Odyssey'?

343
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,080
Why didn't you say it?

344
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:39,360
Everyone is talking about world classics.

345
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:40,520
If I said 'A Chinese Odyssey',

346
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:41,840
wouldn't I be laughed at?

347
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:42,640
That's true.

348
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:48,880
'A Chinese Odyssey'.

349
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,600
'A Chinese Odyssey'?

350
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,580
The one with Stephen Chow?

351
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,120
'A Chinese Odyssey'.

352
00:20:56,280 --> 00:20:57,610
Why did you choose this?

353
00:20:57,680 --> 00:20:59,400
Because all the classmates like it.

354
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,200
Do you like it?

355
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:02,120
What about you?

356
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:02,600
I like it.

357
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:03,240
And you?

358
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:05,920
See? The classmates all like it.

359
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:06,880
Meng Jingu,

360
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,600
you support this too?

361
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:11,160
'A Chinese Odyssey' has elements of a Chinese classic,

362
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:12,360
comedy and tragedy,

363
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,600
and it fits the aesthetics of today's young people.

364
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,000
This movie is

365
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,320
quite popular among young people.

366
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,380
Since it's a drama,

367
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:20,680
no one says it has to be played like a classic.

368
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,410
We can take a different approach and be original.

369
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,440
Maybe we can win at one stroke.

370
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:27,240
That sounds good.

371
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:28,400
Sit down.

372
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,520
So, what does everyone think?

373
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,560
Sure, it's good.

374
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:33,120
Agree.

375
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,480
Let's perform this, sir.

376
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,080
All right.

377
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,480
Since you have decided,

378
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,720
let's perform 'A Chinese Odyssey'.

379
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:40,240
Although I think this is a bit risky,

380
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:41,560
I'll say it again:

381
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,720
As long as you work together

382
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,120
and try your best in this competition,

383
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:46,980
you are the champions in my heart.

384
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:47,560
Okay.

385
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,600
Since we are going to participate in the competition,

386
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:54,120
should we

387
00:21:54,120 --> 00:21:55,720
choose a captain to plan it?

388
00:21:56,480 --> 00:21:57,360
Meng Jingu

389
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:59,040
used to be a student council cadre

390
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,440
when he was in Peiying Middle School,

391
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:03,120
and he participated in the school anniversary of Peiying Middle School.

392
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:03,960
So in this aspect,

393
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:05,440
they might have more experience.

394
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:06,370
So I propose that

395
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:08,680
Meng Jingu and the class monitor, Xing Yaqi,

396
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:09,840
be in charge of this planning.

397
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:11,160
Does anyone have any objections?

398
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,280
No.

399
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:15,600
Okay, as for the participants,

400
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:17,000
you can decide for yourselves.

401
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,200
Voluntary sign-up is fine,

402
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,120
and voting by everyone is also fine.

403
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:21,680
But let me make it clear first.

404
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,240
The midterm exams are coming up soon,

405
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,320
so studies come first.

406
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:27,440
Especially the bottom ten students in the monthly exam,

407
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:28,600
if you don't do well this time,

408
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:29,800
see how I'll deal with you.

409
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,720
Got it.

410
00:22:32,880 --> 00:22:35,640
I'm looking forward to Yuanbao's version of Fairy Zixia.

411
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:38,440
Also, whose turn is it for classroom duty?

412
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:39,280
Teacher,

413
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:40,560
our group.

414
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:41,480
Gao Jingyi,

415
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:42,880
regarding the toilets today,

416
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:43,840
we still need two people to clean.

417
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:44,900
Please arrange it.

418
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:46,440
But, um,

419
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:48,560
Wang Fei and Zhang Jiadong took sick leave today.

420
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:49,560
They didn't come.

421
00:22:49,880 --> 00:22:51,880
It seems we don't have enough people.

422
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:53,600
Are there any students

423
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,480
who would volunteer to clean the toilets?

424
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:56,810
Who would be so foolish?

425
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:58,800
Teacher,

426
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:00,480
I

427
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:02,120
volunteer.

428
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:04,280
There really is someone so foolish.

429
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:06,800
Yuanbao, one person might not be enough.

430
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:08,080
Teacher,

431
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:09,800
leave it to me.

432
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:11,240
I can do it alone.

433
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,480
Okay, thanks for your hard work, Yuanbao.

434
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:15,560
If you need more hands, remember to find a helper.

435
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:16,440
Okay, sir.

436
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:18,480
Alright, class dismissed.

437
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:19,960
School is over!

438
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:21,040
Let's go home.

439
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:05,280
Our school used to be

440
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:07,000
a prince's mansion.

441
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,760
When the whole family was executed,

442
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:12,160
many infants under a month old were killed.

443
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,800
When night falls,

444
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:17,420
they come out to seek revenge.

445
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:23,760
Help!

446
00:24:24,280 --> 00:24:25,400
There's a ghost!

447
00:24:40,760 --> 00:24:41,560
What's wrong?

448
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:44,640
There's a ghost inside!

449
00:24:58,760 --> 00:24:59,560
A ghost?

450
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,370
I think you just have a guilty conscience.

451
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,400
No.

452
00:25:03,520 --> 00:25:05,840
Listen, there really is a sound inside.

453
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:07,240
It's so scary.

454
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:09,720
Wait a minute.

455
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:11,440
Wait, don't go in.

456
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:15,340
There's nothing here.

457
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:23,690
This side up.

458
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:29,440
It's just a little kitty.

459
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:32,600
Why is it crying like that? It's so scary.

460
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:33,810
Special period.

461
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:35,440
What special period?

462
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:36,570
You don't know this?

463
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:37,800
Animals

464
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,240
go through something called heat.

465
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,570
When they're in heat...

466
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:44,080
Stop talking.

467
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,400
I get it. I get it.

468
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,800
Why are you two here?

469
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,360
To see if you need help.

470
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:58,880
The teacher asked me to come and check.

471
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:00,480
The teacher didn't ask me to come.

472
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:02,280
But we live opposite each other.

473
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:08,640
Since you're done cleaning, I'll get going.

474
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:09,640
Wait. Wait.

475
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:11,320
Why don't we go together?

476
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,720
It's all Shang Ningyu's fault.

477
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,040
Telling ghost stories every day.

478
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,100
Scared me to death.

479
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:17,640
Mr. Liu.

480
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:18,480
Hello,

481
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:19,240
Mr. Liu.

482
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,560
You scared me.

483
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,560
Why haven't you left yet?

484
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:25,160
Xiong Yuanbao just finished cleaning the restrooms on two floors.

485
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:26,520
Okay, I'm leaving then.

486
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:29,520
Wait.

487
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:32,720
I'm here to use the restroom.

488
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:35,700
You scared me so much I almost forgot.

489
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:36,720
Well,

490
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,800
Mr. Liu, should we wait for you?

491
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:41,880
No need. You'll affect my performance if you stay here.

492
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:43,480
Alright, we'll leave first.

493
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:49,160
Won't Mr. Liu be scared alone?

494
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,760
You think everyone is like you?

495
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:53,620
There are no ghosts in this world.

496
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:55,300
They're all made up by people.

497
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,680
I know,

498
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,280
but I'm still scared.

499
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:02,240
If you're really scared,

500
00:27:02,680 --> 00:27:03,640
you can sing.

501
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:05,960
The funnier the song, the better the effect.

502
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:06,720
Give it a try.

503
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:08,640
Really? I'll try it.

504
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:12,000
The river flows east.

505
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:14,530
The stars in the sky follow the Big Dipper.

506
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:19,200
I think I feel a bit better.

507
00:27:20,080 --> 00:27:22,440
Give a roar when you see injustice.

508
00:27:22,480 --> 00:27:24,520
Strike when it's time to strike.

509
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:26,040
Are you crazy?

510
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:33,560
Desk mate,

511
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:34,970
I'll be leaving now.

512
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:36,880
Okay, bye.

513
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:38,200
See you tomorrow.

514
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:39,800
See you tomorrow.

515
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:40,920
Bye.

516
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:45,200
Why are you so nice to your desk mate?

517
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:47,640
He's a new classmate,

518
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:48,720
and my desk mate.

519
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:50,360
He also helped me.

520
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:52,760
What's wrong with being polite to him?

521
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:54,200
What, are you jealous?

522
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:56,600
Me, jealous?

523
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,400
Are you thinking too highly of him,

524
00:27:58,400 --> 00:27:59,760
or too highly of yourself?

525
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,280
Why would I be jealous?

526
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,680
Why are you so mad?

527
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,080
Didn't you already go back?

528
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,420
Why are you here again?

529
00:28:08,640 --> 00:28:11,240
I just forgot something and came back to get it.

530
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,320
Thanks for today.

531
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:16,320
For what?

532
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:19,320
Thanks for suggesting to everyone

533
00:28:19,360 --> 00:28:21,420
that we perform "A Chinese Odyssey".

534
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,280
I just said it in passing.

535
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:25,400
It wasn't for you.

536
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:27,720
You're not nice to me at all.

537
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,680
Why would I suggest performing "A Chinese Odyssey" for you?

538
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,080
Don't flatter yourself.

539
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,220
Who do you want to play?

540
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:37,930
After thinking it over,

541
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:40,680
Great Immortal Pansi suits me best.

542
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:43,560
I'll just compromise

543
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:45,410
and play Great Immortal Pansi.

544
00:28:45,760 --> 00:28:47,160
Compromise?

545
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,660
Don't you just want to play Zixia?

546
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:51,160
Yeah, so what?

547
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,730
What do you want to play?

548
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:54,880
Since you're playing Zixia,

549
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:56,520
then I...

550
00:28:58,880 --> 00:28:59,520
Since we were kids,

551
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:00,600
for this kind of performance,

552
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:02,080
haven't you always been the boss?

553
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:03,520
I'm hungry. Let's go eat.

554
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,680
Why are you eating again?

555
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,880
How about you play Zhu Bajie?

556
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:10,320
You're the biggest eater here.

557
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,800
You should play Zhu Bajie.

558
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:13,680
How about you play the Bull Demon King?

559
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:15,120
Then you play the Spider Demon.

560
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:15,760
Bull Demon King!

561
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:16,320
Spider Demon!

562
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:16,960
You are the Bull Demon King!

563
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:18,690
Spider Demon! Bull Demon King!

564
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,560
You're so silly.

565
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,530
Look at me, the Pansi Fairy.

566
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:31,280
So silly.

567
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:43,120
I'm not afraid to be alone.

568
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:45,200
Courage as my blanket.

569
00:29:45,760 --> 00:29:48,120
Not afraid.

570
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:53,520
No matter how dark the night is, I'll pretend not to see.

571
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:57,360
The sun will definitely appear.

572
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:59,440
Hello, look at me.

573
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:01,320
What are you afraid of?

574
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:11,520
Aren't you going on a business trip in a couple of days?

575
00:30:11,960 --> 00:30:13,520
Let's go see them first.

576
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:16,440
Okay, let's go early tomorrow morning.

577
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,450
It's been so many years.

578
00:30:25,520 --> 00:30:29,200
They should be the ones visiting us.

579
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:36,440
All right, all right.

580
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:39,080
Keep it a secret.

581
00:30:40,160 --> 00:30:41,640
We can never let the kids know.
